# Tally Counter REST API

## Overview

Tally Counter build with Node.js, Express and Winston.
Counter can be read, increased or reset.

## Installation

npm init -y
npm install --save winston@3.11.0

## Running the server

node src/main.js

Server runs on http://localhost:3000

## Endpoints

[ENDPOINT] GET '/counter-read' = Get the current counter value
[ENDPOINT] GET '/counter-increase' = Increment counter by 1
[ENDPOINT] GET '/counter-reset' = Reset counter to 0

## Logging

All events are logged to console and app.log.
